From: Daniel Bozeman <daniel@orb.net>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 18:02:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] pmdomain/rockchip: skip domains returning -EPROBE_DEFER

rockchip_pm_domain_probe() iterates the power-domain child nodes and
calls rockchip_pm_add_one_domain() for each. When one domain's clock
lookup returns -EPROBE_DEFER (e.g. RK3528 PD_GPU waiting on the SCMI
clock controller), the whole controller probe fails and tears down
every domain that already registered successfully.

On RK3528 this leaves PD_RKVENC unregistered while a GPIO4 consumer
(USB VBUS regulator) probes, accessing a powered-down domain and
faulting with a synchronous external abort (clk_gate_endisable), and
can corrupt timer state (run_timer_softirq NULL deref).

Skip nodes that defer and continue registering the rest; their
consumers get -ENOENT and defer their own probe until the domain is
available.

Fixes: 7c696693a4f5 ("pmdomain: rockchip: Add power domain support")
Signed-off-by: Daniel Bozeman <daniel@orb.net>

Backported from linux-pm:
https://lore.kernel.org/linux-pm/20260331180223.1682283-1-daniel@orb.net/ (2/2)
---
 drivers/pmdomain/rockchip/pm-domains.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/pmdomain/rockchip/pm-domains.c
+++ b/drivers/pmdomain/rockchip/pm-domains.c
@@ -1057,6 +1057,11 @@ static int rockchip_pm_domain_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	for_each_available_child_of_node_scoped(np, node) {
 		error = rockchip_pm_add_one_domain(pmu, node);
 		if (error) {
+			if (error == -EPROBE_DEFER) {
+				dev_dbg(dev, "skipped node %pOFn, dependencies not yet available\n",
+					node);
+				continue;
+			}
 			dev_err(dev, "failed to handle node %pOFn: %d\n",
 				node, error);
 			goto err_out;
